## Reflection on SMILE Methodology
SMILE feels more like a systems engineering mindset rather than just a methodology. What stood out to me is its emphasis on designing systems that enforce behavior automatically instead of relying on manual rules or policies. This aligns with how scalable AI systems should work, where reliability comes from architecture rather than user discipline. It also connects well with the idea of digital twins, where continuous data tracking and lifecycle understanding are essential for meaningful insights. Overall, it shifts the focus from just building models to understanding how systems behave over time.
